# Use of dictionary in Python

# A dictionay contains key:value pair. To access the values we can use the key.

    students = { "Rachel": 12, "Bob":17, "Emily":15 }

# How to display a specific value

    students["Rachel"] # this will output value 12

# How to update a value in a dictionary

    students["Emily"] = 16 # Update the value 15 into 16
